        "answer": "Mike Portnoy recorded Six Degrees of Inner Turbulence (2002) on a Tama Starclassic Maple kit — the same shell platform he had used on Scenes from a Memory (1999), now configured with a midnight blue sparkle finish. The setup featured double 22\"x18\" bass drums and six toms ranging from 8\" to 16\". The Starclassic Maple's warm, resonant character served both the aggressive Disc 1 material and the dynamic range required across the 42-minute title suite on Disc 2. For more on his gear history, see the [Mike Portnoy drummer profile](/drummer/mike-portnoy)."
