      "size": "14\" x 6.5\"",
      "shell": "Maple",
      "description": "Portnoy's matching Tama Starclassic Maple snare provided the warm, authoritative crack that anchors *Nightmare*'s production. The 6.5\" depth offered the balance of power and sensitivity that the album's dynamic range demanded — from the brutal snare hits of \"God Hates Us\" and \"Natural Born Killer\" to the restrained, measured backbeat of \"So Far Away.\"\n\nThe maple shell's character complemented the album's emotional register. Maple snares produce a fuller, more mid-forward snap than metal or birch alternatives — a sound that sits in heavy guitar mixes without becoming harsh. On *Nightmare*, where the emotional content of the songs required the drums to support rather than dominate, this character was exactly right.\n\nTuned in the medium range for the sessions, the snare delivered clear attack for metal passages while retaining the sensitivity for dynamic variation that The Rev's original compositions required. Portnoy's task was to replicate The Rev's drum voice as faithfully as possible — and the Starclassic Maple snare's versatile character gave him the range to do that.",
